    "updated_at": "2026-03-29T16:51:07Z",
    "dependencies": [
      {
        "id": "noscope-cg8",
        "title": "API DX/AX hardening and deduplication",
        "description": "Context: current library is policy-rich but ergonomics are low. Public API is module-level helpers with no cohesive façade; there is duplication across config/path/capabilities parsing and token envelope handling. This epic tracks API DX + agent experience (AX) improvements without changing security invariants.\\n\\nGoals:\\n- Provide a cohesive, minimal public API for common workflows\\n- Reduce cross-module duplication to lower maintenance cost\\n- Move CLI-specific parsing/argv concerns out of core library APIs\\n- Unify error surfaces into structured, machine-usable types\\n\\nNon-goals:\\n- Relaxing any token redaction/zeroization/security guarantees\\n- Rewriting existing tested policy logic unless required by API shape\\n\\nSuccess criteria:\\n- Consumers can perform run/mint/revoke flows via high-level API\\n- Core modules expose fewer stringly helper APIs\\n- Duplicated config/path/capability parsing responsibilities are consolidated\\n- AX improves via typed errors/events suitable for agents",
        "status": "open",
